  "runtime": {
    "_notes": [
      "tiled CNN conv -- ONE K-tile chunk (K_TILE=4). For the default K=4 this is a complete conv reduction; for K>4 the host relaunches this chain ceil(K/4) times.",
      "4 CTAs x 16 threads = 64 output elements.",
      "Per K-tile launch: host re-stages csrX0 (patch base) + csrX1 (weight base) to the tile's slice; csrX2 (C base) stays fixed.",
      "C buffer is host-zeroed before K-tile 0; every chunk does load_C -> accum -> store_C so the math is uniform across tiles.",
      "out[t] += sum_{k in tile} patch[k,t] * weight[k,t].",
      "Per-CTA shift (+16): csrX0/csrX1/csrX2. Memory layout matches scripts/gemm so the host im2col/packing code is shared."
    ],
